The 106 km race will take the participants through a challenging route which includes thick pine forests, streams and rivulets, treacherous mountain roads and village back roads. Participants from seven countries including US, UK, Australia and New Zealand are taking part in the race. A participant, Foram Veera, said mountain biking was gaining popularity in India and the race gave those passionate about it a platform to showcase their skills. The bikers will camp in forest overnight. The race will conclude on Sunday and the winner will take home a cash prize of rupees 650,000 ($9,966). --news24--